items.name: New York Times Page 1
items.description:
This is an odd one. It's an embedding trained on 20 images of a day's Page 1 of The New York Times.

Honestly, I expected the outputs here to be more consistent, given that many elements of the layout are identical from day to day (most obviously the top nameplate and ears). But the variations are actually rather striking, bringing in a bolder use of imagery that's more associated with certain European or Latin American newspapers (or, more often, magazines). It seems to really like abstract oceanscapes and glaciers.

It's not especially responsive to prompting, but I can imagine it being useful for layout inspiration; certainly it produces more visual interest than most newspaper front pages.

Because of the Times' broadsheet layout, this TI is trained on 512x930 images — 0.004 learning rate, batch size 4, gradient steps 5, 200 total steps.

items.name: USSR Bus Liaz-677 (СССР Автобус Лиаз-677 Скотовоз)

modelVersions.name: v1.0
modelVersions.description:
ЛиАЗ-677 — советский и российский городской высокопольный автобус производства Ликинского автобусного завода. Всего было выпущено около 200 000 автобусов всех модификаций (самая массовая модель завода).

Первый опытный экземпляр автобуса был выпущен в 1963 году. Массово выпускался с 1967 по 1994 год; штучная сборка на сторонних автосборочных предприятиях из машинокомплектов продолжалась до 2002 года. ЛиАЗ-677 является первым советским автобусом с гидромеханической (автоматической) коробкой переключения передач. Автобусы этой модели использовались практически во всех городах Советского Союза, имеющих городское или пригородное автобусное сообщение. Имеет прозвище «Скотовоз» или «Луноход». С начала 2000-х годов модель постепенно выводили из эксплуатации.

该lora不需要触发词，主要作用在脸型，对皮肤调节力度不大

经测试，在majicmixRealistic、墨幽人造人、moonfilm等写实模型上表现良好，不会对脸型和皮肤（一丢丢）以外有过多影响，叠加NWSJ、Koreandolllikeness等人脸lora的效果也很好；

在二次元模型如meinamix、anything上的作用力不强，如需调节二次元人物脸型可能需要加更高的权重，但麻瓜发现就算变化小也基本不会破坏画面构图。

该lora训练时长超过30个小时，制作过程实属不易，喜欢的话务必给我点赞、返图和评论，如有测试反馈欢迎评论区留言告诉我！后续会进一步进行优化！

Do you have any preferences when it comes to facial shapes? Do you prefer an almond-shaped face or a small round face?

Spending a whole night running hundreds of images, selecting just a few dozen you desire, and then individually editing each one in Photoshop to modify their facial shapes – doesn't that sound exhausting? Moreover, using editing software can be troublesome, with the risk of losing quality due to compression when passing files back and forth.

From a professional perspective, the most popular face model, Lora, when used with the adetailer plugin, can only replace facial features but cannot alter the facial shape generated by the base model. This could significantly reduce the similarity to the original face after modifications.

To address this, Muggle proudly presents the Lora Facial Shape Adjustment Tool. The reasonable weight range is -1.5 to 1.5 (going beyond might not cause crashes but may not yield desirable results, so adjust according to individual needs).

Negative weights will produce an almond-shaped face with fairer skin tones. Positive weights will result in a small round face with slightly rosy skin tones. Lora primarily focuses on facial shape adjustment, with minimal impact on skin tones.

Through testing, it performs excellently on realistic models like majicmixRealistic, moyourenzaoren, moonfilm, preserving facial shape and skin characteristics (to a minimal extent) while also working well when combined with NWSJ, Koreandolllikeness, and other facial Lora models.

For anime models like meinamix and anything, its impact is less pronounced. If you need to adjust the facial shape of anime characters, a higher weight might be necessary. Nonetheless, even with slight changes, Muggle found that it rarely disrupts the composition of the artwork.

The training process for Lora lasted over 30 hours, making its creation no easy task. If you like it, be sure to give it a thumbs-up, share your results, and leave comments. If you have any testing feedback, please feel free to share it in the comments. Further optimizations will be carried out in the future!

【麻瓜lora】笑容大小调节神器

在SD中传统控制笑容大小的办法是写入expressionless、smile、(happy,smile)、(grin,teeth)、laughing、(laughing,open mouth:1.3)等tag

不得不说切换表情的操作实在是繁琐至极，而且在laughing上的表现力经常很差，尤其是当使用人物lora时非常容易受到底模中laughing素材的影响导致面部相似度降低；

所以麻瓜出品了这个笑容大小调节器来代替繁杂的tag，另外部分人物lora在训练时可能缺少笑容素材无法做出很好的笑容表情，可以用这个lora试试看。

与上次发布的脸型大小调节神器不同，笑容大小调节器同时在写实模型和动漫模型上都有着良好的表现，并且几乎不会对原有的人物脸型、五官、皮肤有任何影响。

喜欢的话务必给我点赞、返图和评论，如有测试反馈欢迎评论区留言告诉我！后续会进一步进行优化！

In SD, the traditional way to control the size of smiles is by using tags such as "expressionless," "smile," "(happy, smile)," "(grin, teeth)," "laughing," "(laughing, open mouth: 1.3)," and others. Switching expressions this way can be extremely cumbersome, and the performance of "laughing" expressions is often lacking, especially when using the character "Lora," which is easily affected by the base model's "laughing" materials, resulting in decreased facial similarity.

To address this issue, Muggle has developed the "Smile Size Adjuster" to replace the complex use of tags. Additionally, for some characters like "Lora," who may lack sufficient smile-related materials during training, this tool can be used to achieve better smile expressions.

Unlike the previously released Face Shape Adjuster, the Smile Size Adjuster performs well on both realistic and anime-style models, with virtually no impact on the original character's face shape, facial features, or skin.

If you like it, please give it a thumbs up, share your images, and leave comments. If you have any test feedback, feel free to leave a message in the comments section. Further optimizations will be made in the future!

items.name: Hairloss Concept
items.description: Introducing the Hairloss concept LoRA model for Stable Diffusion 1.5. Enhance your creative process with the addition of a unique hair loss concept, offering a variety of styles to diversify your generated images. With this LoRA, you can easily incorporate features like receding hairlines, thinning hair, buzzcuts, combovers, power donuts, and even the daring skullet! Unleash a new level of possibilities for character design, storytelling, and artistic expression with this model. It works well across a large variety of checkpoint models, including Deliberate, Realistic Vision, Protogen, and more. For most cases, I would recommend using the LoRA at a strength of 0.7 or 0.8. The trigger word is "hairloss" and supplimented by additional terms for styles such as "balding", "combover", "thinning hair", "skullet", "buzz cut", "high widows' peak".
